'''''Young Jedi Knights: Delusions of Grandeur''''' is a [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] young-adult novel written by [[Kevin J. Anderson]] and [[Rebecca Moesta]]. It is the ninth book in the ''[[Star Wars: Young Jedi Knights]]'' series, and it was first published by [[Berkley Boulevard]] in [[July]] [[1997]].

The novel was reprinted in ''[[Young Jedi Knights: The Fall of the Diversity Alliance]]'' ([[1998]]).

==Publisher's summary==
''As the search for Raynar Thul's father continues, the young Jedi Knights turn for help to a most unusual&mdash;and dangerous&mdash;source: the reprogrammed assassin droid IG-88. They think they can keep him under control. But can one of the most feared bounty hunters in the galaxy be trusted?''

==Plot summary==
After seeing his uncle kidnapped, [[Raynar Thul|Raynar]] decides to take over [[Tyko Thul]]'s [[Droid/Legends|droid]]-manufacturing operation on [[Mechis III/Legends|Mechis III]]. He is shocked to find Tycho there. Tyko explains that he reprogramed [[IG-88 assassin droid/Legends|IG-88]] to create the illusion that he was kidnapped, in the hope that word of such a fate might provoke [[Bornan Thul]] to reveal himself.

Tyko is right. Bornan Thul does surface, as an anonymous, disguised [[Gender/Legends|man]] who hires [[Zekk]] to find Tyko and pass a message on to the [[House of Thul|Thul family]]. Zekk's search brings him to [[Ziost/Legends|Ziost]], where he is chased by the [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] [[Dengar/Legends|Dengar]]; to [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]], where he seeks advice from [[Boba Fett/Legends|Boba Fett]]; and finally to Mechis III, where he joins with his friends in the search for Bornan. 

[[Nolaa Tarkona]] – leader of the [[Diversity Alliance]] – continues her plot against humanity. The [[Emperor's Plague|plague]] she used on [[Gammalin]] was part of a sample created by the [[Palpatine/Legends|Emperor]]. Only Bornan Thul knows where further supplies of the [[Poison/Legends|toxin]] can be found, making it imperative that the Diversity Alliance find him. [[Raabakyysh|Raaba]] the [[Wookiee/Legends|Wookiee]] arrives on [[Yavin 4/Legends|Yavin 4]], imploring [[Lowbacca]] to return with her to meet with Tarkona. 

==Continuity==
Lusa identifies [[Hethrir]] as a Human, when he is actually a [[Near-Human]] [[Firrerreo/Legends|Firrerreo]].

